Meet the penguins

palmerpenguins dataは、 ペンギンの体長や血液型などについて 三つの種類と三つの地域で三年にわたり観測されたものである。

ペンギンの絵についてはここから確認ができる.

  • bill: くちばし
  • flipper: ヒレ
penguins

Highliths

ggplot(
  data = penguins, 
  aes (x = flipper_length_mm, y = body_mass_g)
) + 
  geom_point(
    aes(color = species, shape = species), size = 2
  ) + 
  scale_color_manual(values = c("darkorange", "darkorchid", "cyan4")) +

マクロで見ると負の相関だけど、データを分割してみると、負の相関が 見える、ということがわかりやすく示せるデータになる.

ggplot(data = penguins, aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm)) + 
  geom_point(size = 2) + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE)

上記の線形回帰を種類別に記述すると次のようになる。

ggplot(data = penguins, aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = species, 
                 shape = species), 
             size = 2) + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, aes(color = species)) + 
  scale_color_manual(values = c("darkorange", "darkorchid", "cyan4"))

penguins_corr <- 
  penguins %>%
  dplyr::select(body_mass_g, ends_with("_mm")) %>%
  correlate() %>%
  rearrange()

PCA

recipesパッケージを使う. PCAを使う前処理として次が必要である.

  • remove any NA values
  • center all predictors and scale all predictors
penguin_recipe <- 
  recipe( ~ ., data = penguins) %>%
  update_role(species, island, sex, year, new_role = "id") %>%
  step_naomit(all_predictors()) %>%
  step_normalize(all_predictors()) %>%
  step_pca(all_predictors(), id = "pca") %>%
  prep()
penguin_pca <- 
  penguin_recipe %>%
  tidy(id = "pca")

penguin_pca
penguins %>%
  dplyr::select(body_mass_g, ends_with("_mm")) %>%
  tidyr::drop_na() %>%
  scale() %>%
  prcomp() %>%
  .$rotation
##                          PC1         PC2        PC3        PC4
## body_mass_g        0.5483502 0.084362920 -0.5966001 -0.5798821
## bill_length_mm     0.4552503 0.597031143  0.6443012 -0.1455231
## bill_depth_mm     -0.4003347 0.797766572 -0.4184272  0.1679860
## flipper_length_mm  0.5760133 0.002282201 -0.2320840  0.7837987

PCAの寄与度を可視化する.

penguin_recipe %>%
  tidy(id = "pca", type = "variance") %>%
  dplyr::filter(terms == "percent variance") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = component, y = value)) +
  geom_col(fill = "#b6dfe2") +
  xlim(c(0, 5)) +
  ylab("% of total variance")

Plot PCA loadings

library(ggplot2)
penguin_pca %>%
  mutate(terms = tidytext::reorder_within(terms,
                                          abs(value),
                                          component)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(abs(value), terms, fill = value > 0)) +
  geom_col() +
  facet_wrap(~component, scales = "free_y") +
  tidytext::scale_y_reordered() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#b6dfe2", "#0A537D")) +
  labs(
    x = "Absolute value of contribution",
    y = NULL, fill = "Positive?"
  )

Plot PCA loadings + scores

pca_wider <- 
  penguin_pca %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = component, id_cols = terms)
# define arrow style
arrow_style <- 
  arrow(
    length = unit(.05, "inches"), 
    type = "closed"
  )

pca_plot <-
  juice(penguin_recipe) %>%
  ggplot(aes(PC1, PC2)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = species, shape = species), 
             alpha = .8, size = 2) + 
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("darkorange", "purple", "cyan4"))

pca_plot + 
  geom_segment(data = pca_wider, 
               aes(xend = PC1, yend = PC2), 
               x = 0, y = 0, arrow = arrow_style) + 
  geom_text(data = pca_wider, 
            aes(x = PC1, y = PC2, label = terms), 
            hjust = 0, 
            vjust = 1, 
            size  = 5, 
            color = "#0A537D")

なんというか、このグラフのわかりやすさには驚嘆せざるを得ない。 filpper_length_mmとbody_mass_gが同様にPC1に効いていることがわかる。 そしてPC1により、Gentoo種とその他の種が分離できそうなことがわかる.

penguins %>%
  group_by(species) %>%
  select(flipper_length_mm, body_mass_g) %>%
  summarise_all(mean, na.rm = TRUE)
## Adding missing grouping variables: `species`
